27
00:02:24,560 --> 00:02:29,039
Also I hear that over a certain temperature olive oil turns harmful.

28
00:02:29,039 --> 00:02:35,919
What the heck do I use for frying and roasting? Greg says that he's received a walkload of emails.

29
00:02:36,479 --> 00:02:43,519
A load of something is a lot of something. You'll also commonly hear the expression shed load or truck load.

30
00:02:43,519 --> 00:02:46,719
These are used to emphasise how much of something there is.

31
00:02:46,719 --> 00:02:52,400
Yes and Greg uses walkload as a fun expression because he's talking about cooking oils and a

32
00:02:52,400 --> 00:02:58,000
walk is a kind of pan. Greg reads one of the emails from a confused listener, Alistair,

33
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:04,079
who says that he's watched YouTube videos that argue that oils like sunflower oil are bad for you.

34
00:03:04,560 --> 00:03:10,719
These videos advocate using extra virgin olive oil. If you advocate something you encourage

35
00:03:10,719 --> 00:03:16,000
people to use it. But Alistair has also heard bad things about olive oil and that you

36
